<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1008,2042]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1183,1209]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 15.5–15.8; head length: 1.6–1.7; head width: 3.1; pronotal length: 2.8–3.0; pronotal width: 9.6–9.7; scutellum length: 7.0–7.2; scutellum width: 5.4–6.6; abdominal width: 8.4–8.6; length of antennal segments. I: 1.0; II: 1.6–1.8; III: 1.0–1.1; IV: 4.3; V: missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1008,2042]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1286,1312]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum without dark stripe. Anterolateral margin scarcely punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1146,1321,1347]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin concolorous (
<figureCitation box="[391,497,1356,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with light brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[981,1085,1356,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1425,1356,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dorsal rim slightly convex medially (
<figureCitation box="[687,791,1391,1417]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup rectangular, flat dorsally, thin, ventrally with a conical projection; adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1249,1425,1451]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere clublike, head almost entirely black; anterior lobe large and truncated; posterior lobe well-developed and rounded; inner face of the stalk with carina evanescent ending at posterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[890,1026,1495,1521]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of long setae separated by dorsal broad ridge; posterior face pentagonal (
<figureCitation box="[937,1077,1529,1555]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13A–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with median excavation wide; expansions acuminated and slightly bent inwards; surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[222,327,1599,1625]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[552,654,1599,1625]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 13E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 with posterior margin sinuous and sloping, inner angles acuminated and reaching base of valvifers 9; inner margins slightly divergent on distal half, median excavation cup like and broad. Valvulae 8 exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1008,2042]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1702,1728]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Comments</emphasis>
. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[393,547,1703,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[393,547,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[603,783,1703,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[603,783,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[837,1075,1703,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassimarginatum">
<emphasis box="[837,1075,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. crassimarginatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the head of the paramere broad with posterior lobe well-developed and rounded to acuminated, anterior lobe somewhat developed and round- ed to truncated (
<figureCitation box="[330,475,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Figs. 13B–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[485,568,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">16B–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[578,648,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777068/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">4B–C</figureCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[715,868,1773,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[715,868,1773,1798]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1073,1252,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1252,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the shape of the superior process of the genital cup, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[658,811,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[658,811,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the ventral conical projection of superior process of the genital cup situated anteriorly (mesially in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[716,897,1841,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[716,897,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); posterior lobe of paramere short and truncate (longer and rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[419,599,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[419,599,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and expansions of ventral rim acuminated (rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1247,1427,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1427,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[159,305,1911,1937]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Hypoxys runcinatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777086/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Figs. 13B–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[316,400,1911,1937]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">16B–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1008,2042]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1945,1971]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the plain dorsal surface of superior process of the genital cup (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1218,1338,1946,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runcinatus">
<emphasis box="[1218,1338,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">runcinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= plane, flattened).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
